# Plumbing SlatePress design system (plumbingslatepress-com-site repo)

This rule encodes the canonical brand tokens for **plumbingslatepress.com** specifically. Each SlatePress vertical-brand repo has its own `:root` block; this rule is repo-scoped and applies only to plumbingslatepress-com-site edits.

The source of truth for these tokens is the `:root` block at the top of `index.html`. If they ever drift, this rule should be updated to match - the live file wins.

## Canonical tokens

```css
:root{
  --accent:#2563EB;
  --accent-glow:rgba(37,99,235,.14);

  --paper:#FAFBFF;          /* primary paper-tinted page canvas */
  --paper-2:#EEF3FF;        /* secondary surface, slightly bluer */
  --paper-3:#E1EAFF;        /* tertiary surface, distinctly blue */
  --white:#FFFFFF;          /* card / contrast surface */

  --ink:#0A0A0A;            /* primary text, near-black */
  --ink-soft:#3A3D42;       /* secondary text */
  --slate:#6B6A73;          /* tertiary text */

  --rule:#DCE3F5;           /* default 1px borders */
  --rule-soft:#E8EDFA;      /* subtle dividers */

  --blue:#2563EB;           /* PRIMARY BRAND BLUE - logo "/" + primary CTAs */
  --blue-deep:#1D4ED8;      /* hover state for blue */
  --blue-bright:#3B82F6;    /* lighter accent variant */
  --blue-soft:#EFF3FF;      /* light blue tint for backgrounds/badges */
  --blue-glow:rgba(37,99,235,.16);

  --max:1240px;             /* content max-width - wider than slatepress.co's 1080 */
}
```

## Type stack

**Inter only.** Single sans-serif throughout. No display serif, no monospace by default.

```css
font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
```

## Cardinal rules for plumbingslatepress-com-site

- **Paper-tinted canvas (`--paper`).** Slightly cooler than pure white - this is the trade-vertical signal that distinguishes plumbing from the slatepress.co parent (which uses pure `--bg #FFFFFF`). Sections step down to `--paper-2` and `--paper-3` for visual rhythm.
- **Brand blue (`--blue` #2563EB) is the one accent.** Logo `/`, primary CTAs, focus rings, at most one emphasis moment per viewport. No second accent color. The brand-bright `--blue-bright` is reserved for hover/active states or very small accent moments.
- **`--white` is for contrast surfaces only.** Cards, modal sheets, pricing-card backgrounds. Never for full-page canvases - the paper tint is part of the brand identity.
- **No new hex codes.** If a component needs a color not in `:root`, raise the design-system question before adding. Drift across pages is the failure mode.
- **No gradient buttons, no carousels, no Lorem ipsum, no emoji in production UI.**
- **`--max:1240px`** is wider than slatepress.co (`--max:1080px`). This is intentional - the lander has more business-information content (services, service areas, pricing, comparison table, founders-band). Don't shrink to 1080.

## Pricing pairing

This repo ships the Foundation Founder pricing card synced with slatepress.co. See `pricing-sync.mdc` for the cross-repo discipline. Editing the pricing here without the matching edit on slatepress-site is a customer-trust risk.

## When designing or reviewing UI in this repo

Defer to the `premium-web-designer` Claude skill. It encodes the universal taste rules. This rule supplies the brand-specific tokens it loads when editing plumbingslatepress.com.

When `premium-web-designer` fires, it should:
1. Ask "What are we designing today?"
2. On the answer "plumbingslatepress.com" or any edit in this repo, load the tokens above.
3. Apply universal taste principles on top.
4. Produce code that references the brand's variable names (`--blue`, `--ink`, `--paper`, `--paper-2`) directly - never invent token names.
